{"title":"Crystal ball of fixation","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Crystal_ball_of_fixation","type":"markdown","data":"***Obsolete**: This article refers to an aspect of the game which has been removed. It is retained for historical reference only.*\n\n|   |                                                                                                                                |\n| - | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n|   | A dangerous item which hypnotizes anyone so unwise as to gaze into it, leaving them helpless for a significant length of time. |\n\nA **crystal ball of fixation** is an evocable item which, when used \"successfully\", leaves you [paralyzed](/Paralyze \"Paralyze\") and [slow](/Slow \"Slow\") for 100 turns. This makes you easy prey for any wandering monsters that find you. On a failure, you suffer a [Divinations](/Divinations \"Divinations\") [miscast effect](/Miscast_effect \"Miscast effect\"), such as losing all [MP](/MP \"MP\"), taking [intelligence](/Intelligence \"Intelligence\") damage, or being [confused](/Confused \"Confused\") for 10-20 turns. This item serves no purpose except to make players cautious about testing unidentified crystal balls.\n\n## History\n\nThese were removed in [0.8](/0.8 \"0.8\"). Before that, they were a source of numerous amusing deaths.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Crystal ball of fixation - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Crystal_ball_of_fixation\",\"wgTitle\":\"Crystal ball of fixation\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":84